9, 50%, 50%, .75)') // [87.125, 191.25, 63.75, .75]\nrgba`rgb(80 120 160 / 50%)` // [80, 120, 160, .5]\n```\n\n## API\n\n### `let [r, g, b, alpha] = rgba(color)`\n\nReturns channels values as they are in the input `color` string argument. `alpha` is always from `0..1` range. `color` can be a CSS color string, an array with channel values, an object etc., see [color-parse](https://ghub.io/color-parse).\n\n## Related\n\n* [color-normalize](https://github.com/colorjs/color-normalize) − convert any input color argument into a defined output format.\n* [color-alpha](https://github.com/colorjs/color-alpha) − change alpha of a color string.\n* [color-interpolate](https://github.com/colorjs/color-interpolate) − interpolate by color palette.\n\n## License\n\n(c) 2017 Dima Yv. MIT License\n","maintainers":[{"name":"dfcreative","email":"df.creative@gmail.com"},{"name":"dy","email":"df.creative@gmail.com"}],"time":{"modified":"2023-09-15T19:09:27.157Z","created":"2016-11-15T19:08:17.844Z","1.0.0":"2016-11-15T19:08:17.844Z","1.0.1":"2017-03-03T17:00:33.832Z","1.0.2":"2017-03-03T19:15:53.228Z","1.0.3":"2017-03-03T19:18:20.456Z","1.0.4":"2017-03-03T21:54:25.725Z","1.1.0":"2017-03-04T15:32:35.030Z","1.1.1":"2017-07-26T07:13:21.774Z","2.0.0":"2017-10-24T20:43:31.215Z","2.1.0":"2018-06-22T21:07:39.947Z","2.1.1":"2019-05-25T16:08:34.540Z","2.2.0":"2020-09-26T14:15:18.188Z","2.2.1":"2020-09-28T19:57:37.836Z","2.2.2":"2020-09-28T19:58:56.973Z","2.2.3":"2020-10-02T02:37:12.495Z","2.3.0":"2021-09-09T22:08:55.025Z","2.4.0":"2022-01-25T03:37:42.117Z","3.0.0":"2023-09-15T19:09:26.977Z"},"homepage":"https://github.com/colorjs/color-rgba#readme","keywords":["color","colorjs","rgb","rgba","color-space","css"],"repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/colorjs/color-rgba.git"},"author":{"name":"Dmitry Iv","email":"dfcreative@gmail.com"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/colorjs/color-rgba/issues"},"license":"MIT","readmeFilename":"readme.md"}